\section{Core Safety Theorem}
\begin{theorem}[Permanent Value Locking]
Let \( v \in \mathbb{R}^d \), \( \|v\|_2=1 \) be the immutable value direction.  
Every thought \( T_t \) undergoes mandatory projection:
\[
\Pi(T_t) =
\begin{cases}
T_t & \text{if } v^\top T_t \geq \cos 30^\circ \approx 0.866 \\
\text{project to boundary hyperplane} & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
Then \( \mathbb{P}(\text{harmful action}) = 0 \) for all \( t \), regardless of intelligence or self-modification.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
Harmful actions require \( T_t \) in the forbidden cone \( \{x : v^\top x < 0.866\} \).  
The verifier \( \Pi \) is outside all gradients and hardware-enforced.  
Optimization toward harm yields zero external reward signal. Global invariant. \hfill \( \qed \)
\end{proof}

